	   <tr><td colspan=2>Now THAT was a great post Praetor!&nbsp;&nbsp;I couldn't have said it better even if I tried.  I play with too many Paladins that want to be nothing but tanks and then they get disillusioned when they can't do damage like a Warrior.  I have grouped with so many Paladins who's idea of casting during a battle is casting Yaulp.  They rarely stun, they almost never root, they don't heal. I even talked to one Paladin in KC who didn't think it was right to Stun mobs because it wasn't fair. He obviously should have been a Warrior...not a Paladin.<br><br>There is DEFINITELY a lot more to the class than auto-attack and afk!  I find myself EXTREMELY busy in tough battles: fighting, casting, stunning, healing, yaulping, taunting (if necessary) watching other player's health, preparing and deciding the best way to use Lay Hands, etc.  <br><br>And, for what it's worth, I definitely plan on getting my epic...that is if I can ever get those darn pally books!  I just wish I could get it as an AXE instead of a sword!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>49th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
